ass=title>   Spell research/Vendor Farming</span><hr size=1> There was a brief exchange on the Guild Chat about who was able to get what spell research for what spell today, so I'd like to offer my experiences with finding the missing pieces for your spell research.  Here goes:<br>
<br>
Mage<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/research/Magician/">eq.crgaming.com/research/Magician/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Enchanter<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/research/Enchanter/">eq.crgaming.com/research/Enchanter/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Necro<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/research/Necromancer/">eq.crgaming.com/research/Necromancer/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Reading through these helps you research your spells but won't tell you where to find the mobs you need.  From what I've noticed the mobs that drop the components you need are usually one to four levels higher than you (which means you've got to start grouping for the best chance).  Failing that there's always the standby: Vendor Farming.  Vendor farming is simply going around and looking to see what they're selling in any given area.  The average non-caster peep either doesn't know which Words are for which research (unless informed by his caster friend) or doesn't want to spend time in the Bazaar selling research items unless he's got a Vendor Mule.<br>
<br>
With the advent of Planes of Power, it's not that tough to simply head out to the cities nearby zones that have the mobs that drop your spell research and check out what the nearby vendors are selling.  For example, Lavastorm Mountains is a zone adjacent to Nektulos Forest (Dark Elf greenie zone) and itself is only for levels 12+ to 20, tops.  However, the Druid Ring within and the vendor camp nearby can have spell research for levels well into their thirties and forties.  Why?  Because Lavastorm also has SolA and SolB which are between levels 20 to 50.<br>
<br>
That's it in a nutshell.  The other piece of advice I can offer is that the chance of finding something you need grows the longer Verant Interactive keeps the server up.  Unfortunately, a vendor's inventory gets reset when the severs get brought down for updates.<br>
<br>
Coddington<br>
